ntent":"This invoice is considered a tax invoice for the supply of goods or services to that person by another registered person.","pos":[7988,8109]},{"content":"You can issue self-billed invoices only if you receive approval from the Director General.","pos":[8110,8200]},{"content":"The reference number of the approval must be stated on the self-billed invoice.","pos":[8201,8280]},{"content":"To print a self-billed invoice, the invoice type must be set to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>GST invoice<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and you must enter the approval number on the purchase order header.","pos":[8281,8430],"source":" To print a self-billed invoice, the invoice type must be set to **GST invoice**, and you must enter the approval number on the purchase order header."},{"content":"On the invoice, you will see the following additional information:","pos":[8431,8497]},{"content":"The words “Self-billed invoice” in a prominent place","pos":[8503,8555]},{"content":"The approval number","pos":[8560,8579]},{"content":"The GST summary","pos":[8584,8599]},{"pos":[8604,8615],"content":"GST reports","linkify":"GST reports","nodes":[{"content":"GST reports","pos":[0,11]}]},{"content":"The following out-of-box reports are available to provide details about debit notes, credit notes, supplies, and purchases:","pos":[8616,8739]},{"content":"Customer debit note and credit note list","pos":[8745,8785]},{"content":"Vendor debit note and credit note list","pos":[8790,8828]},{"content":"Supply list by tax code","pos":[8833,8856]},{"content":"Purchase list by tax code","pos":[8861,8886]},{"pos":[8888,9013],"content":"Additionally, a configurable <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>GST report by configuration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> report is provided to meet the following reporting requirements:","source":"Additionally, a configurable **GST report by configuration** report is provided to meet the following reporting requirements:"},{"content":"GST-03","pos":[9019,9025]},{"content":"GST summary sheet","pos":[9030,9047]},{"content":"Total acquisition and input tax","pos":[9052,9083]},{"content":"Total supply and output tax","pos":[9088,9115]},{"content":"Consolidated monthly record of total inputs and outputs of all group members for the taxable period","pos":[9120,9219]},{"content":"These reports are in different formats, but they all display monetary amounts (transaction amount and GST amount) for specific transactions.","pos":[9221,9361]},{"content":"To meet these requirements, you can configure the report content and then generate various reports according to your report configurations.","pos":[9362,9501]},{"content":"You must follow these steps to run the report:","pos":[9502,9548]},{"content":"Define sales tax reporting codes.","pos":[9554,9587]},{"content":"Map sales tax reporting codes to sales tax codes.","pos":[9592,9641]},{"content":"Define the GST report configuration.","pos":[9646,9682]},{"pos":[9687,9734],"content":"Run the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>GST report by configuration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> report.","source":"Run the **GST report by configuration** report."},{"pos":[9740,9774],"content":"Defining sales tax reporting codes","linkify":"Defining sales tax reporting codes","nodes":[{"content":"Defining sales tax reporting codes","pos":[0,34]}]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>GST report by configuration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> report takes advantage of reporting code functions in Microsoft Dynamics 365 for Operations.","pos":[9776,9904],"source":"The **GST report by configuration** report takes advantage of reporting code functions in Microsoft Dynamics 365 for Operations."},{"content":"Sales tax reporting codes collect the information for several sales tax codes onto one report line.","pos":[9905,10004]},{"content":"In a typical setup, there is one sales tax reporting code for every calculated field on reports, and some predetermined reporting codes must be created.","pos":[10005,10157]},{"content":"However, because you can now define your own report configurations and specify which reporting codes to use, no predetermined codes are required.","pos":[10158,10303]},{"content":"No specific report layout has been introduced for Malaysia GST.","pos":[10304,10367]},{"content":"You must use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Default<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> report layout for your reporting codes.","pos":[10368,10436],"source":" You must use the **Default** report layout for your reporting codes."},{"pos":[10442,10494],"content":"Mapping sales tax reporting codes to sales tax codes","linkify":"Mapping sales tax reporting codes to sales tax codes","nodes":[{"content":"Mapping sales tax reporting codes to sales tax codes","pos":[0,52]}]},{"content":"Before values can be calculated and displayed on reports, you must specify a relevant sales tax reporting code for each tax code that is used in the sales tax payment process.","pos":[10496,10671]},{"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Report setup<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab, set a sales tax reporting code in one or more fields for each tax code.","pos":[10672,10772],"source":" On the **Report setup** tab, set a sales tax reporting code in one or more fields for each tax code."},{"pos":[10778,10815],"content":"Defining the GST report configuration","linkify":"Defining the GST report configuration","nodes":[{"content":"Defining the GST report configuration","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"You can create report configurations to meet your reporting requirements.","pos":[10817,10890]},{"content":"Before you create a report configuration, you must determine what types of transactions to include.","pos":[10891,10990]},{"content":"For example, if you create a configuration for GST returns, you can include the following types of transactions.","pos":[10991,11103]},{"content":"GST report configuration name","pos":[11106,11135]},{"content":"Type of transaction","pos":[11137,11156]},{"content":"Transaction amount","pos":[11158,11176]},{"content":"GST amount","pos":[11178,11188]},{"content":"G